<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910916-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>910916-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Sprouse-Reitz Stores Inc.:   Loss of $17.6 Million Posted   For Fiscal Second Quarter</HL><DATE>09/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   STRS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OREGON (ORG)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Sprouse-Reitz Stores Inc. reported a widened fiscalsecond-quarter loss of $17.6 million, or $12.30 a share,including a $17 million pre-tax charge from a previouslyreported restructuring.   Last month, the Portland, Ore., general merchandise storeoperator said it was closing 75 stores and dismissing 650employees in its 10-Western-state operating region. It willcontinue to operate 190 stores, and added in a news releaselast week that it expects to return to profitability in thefourth quarter of its current fiscal year.</LP><TEXT>   In the year-earlier fiscal second quarter, Sprouse-Reitzhad a loss of $347,390, or 24 cents a share. The company saidit changed the way it accounted for inventory effective July30, 1991, which reduced previously reported net losses.   Sales for the latest second quarter, which ended July 30,fell 11% to $46.5 million from $52 million a year earlier,partly reflecting the store closings; same-store salesdeclined 4.8% during the quarter, the company added.   For the 26 weeks ended July 30, the company reported a netloss of $19.8 million, or $13.81 a share, on sales of $91.2million, compared with a loss of $312,250, or 22 cents ashare, on sales of $102.3 million, a year earlier.   The loss was disclosed after markets closed Friday.</TEXT></DOC>